The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 All matches now in Colombo

Colombo: The schedule for Bangladeshs tour of Sri Lanka has been amended with the start date moved forward and all games shifted to Colombo. 

The tourists will arrive on the island on August 25 and start a three-match one-day series on August 31 to be followed by a two-match Test series beginning on September 12. 

R. Premadasa Stadium has also been given a Test for the first time since New Zealand beat Sri Lanka in June 1998. 

THE SCHEDULE 

Aug. 31: First ODI, Sinhalese Sports Club; Sept. 2: Second ODI, R. Premadasa Stadium (D/N); Sept 4: Third ODI, R. Premadasa Stadium (D/N); Sept 7: Three-day practice game, Colombo; Sept 12: First Test, P. Saravanamuttu Stadium; Sept 20: Second Test, R. Premadasa Stadium. 

 (PTI) 




